[[File:Baltazar Mathias Keilhau.jpg|thumb|right|200 px |Keilhau portrayed by [[Christiane Schreiber]]]]
'''Baltazar Mathias Keilhau''' (2 November 1797 &ndash; 1 January 1858) was a Norwegian geologist and mountain pioneer. He was born in [[Gj<U+00F8>vik]]. In 1830 he married Christine Kemp. Keilhau is regarded as the founder of geology in Norway. He lectured at the [[University of Oslo|Royal Frederick University]] in Christiania from 1826, and was appointed professor from 1834.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Balthazar Keilhau |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Inge |last=Bryhni |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Balthazar_Keilhau/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Baltazar Mathias Keilhau |first= |last= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://snl.no/Baltazar_Mathias_Keilhau |language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref> 

[[File:Falketind 1985.jpg|thumb|left|200 px|[[Falketind]] was first climbed in 1820 by Keilhau, [[Christian Peder Bianco Boeck]] and [[Ole Urdi]]]]
Keilhau made the first ascent of [[Falketind]] in 1820 along with two other climbers.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Falketind |first= |last= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://snl.no/Falketind |language=Norwegian|accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref> He has later been labeled the "discoverer" of the mountain range [[Jotunheimen]]. The mountain [[Keilhaus topp]] is named after him.<ref name=nbl/> At Svalbard, the mountain [[Keilhaufjellet]] and the glacier [[Mathiasbreen]] are named after him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Keilhaufjellet |title=Keilhaufjellet (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=30 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Mathiasbreen |title=Mathiasbreen (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=30 July 2013}}</ref>

He was decorated Knight of the [[Order of Vasa]], Knight of the [[Order of the Polar Star]], and Knight of the [[Order of St. Olav]].<ref name=nbl/>

